The paper deals with the problem of characterizing joint probability distributions in distributed coding of correlated sources, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also proposes a new data processing inequality, which is a concept in quantum information theory (cs.ITP). The two specific examples mentioned in the paper, multiple-access channel with correlated sources and multiterminal rate-distortion region, are also topics in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses a new measure of correlation through a spectral method, which is a topic in multimedia (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper proposes new necessary conditions for the two specific examples, which can be seen as a form of machine learning (cs.LG).
